<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
In OS_BinSemGetInfo_Impl the local pointer is declared as a non-const: "OS_impl_binsem_internal_record_t *sem;". The pointer is only used to read fields (sem->current_value) and is not used to modify the object, so it could be const-qualified (const OS_impl_binsem_internal_record_t *sem). Therefore the pointer should be const-qualified per MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>
